  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 20:21",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Chronicles 20:21",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "When he had consulted with the people ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— That is, with the elders and heads of the tribes, who represented the rest. He called a council of war, and it was resolved to appoint ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "singers to go out before the army, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "who had nothing to do but to praise God, to praise his holiness, which is his beauty, to praise him as they did in the temple, that ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "beauty of holiness, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "“with that good old doxology, which eternity itself,” as Henry says, “will not wear threadbare, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Praise the Lord, for his mercy endureth for ever.” ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "By this strange advance to the field of battle, Jehoshaphat showed his firm reliance on the word of God, which enabled him to triumph before the battle, to animate his own men, and confound the enemy.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "20:20-30 Jehoshaphat exhorted his troops to firm faith in God. Faith inspires a man with true courage; nor will any thing help more to the establishing of the heart in shaking times, than a firm belief of the power, and mercy, and promise of God. In all our trust in the Lord, and our praises of him, let us especially look at his everlasting mercy to sinners through Jesus Christ. Never was an army so destroyed as that of the enemy. Thus God often makes wicked people destroy one another. And never was a victory celebrated with more solemn thanksgivings.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
